# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Environment variables template (documentation)
#
# These are the variables the framework reads via process.env.
#   - LOCAL: copy this file to ".env" and fill in your values.
#   - CI:    set as GitHub Secrets if you ever point at a private app.
#
# ".env" is gitignored and must NEVER be committed.
# This ".env.example" has NO real secrets, so it is safe to commit.
#
# The SUT (demo-shop-app) ships with PUBLIC demo credentials, so
# config/environments.ts already falls back to them — a real .env is
# only needed if you point the suite at a private deployment.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Where the System Under Test is reachable.
# Leave unset to let Playwright start the app from ./app (see webServer).
# Set it to skip webServer and target an already-running instance.
# BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Demo credentials (mirror Sauce Demo). Defaults are baked in.
DEMO_USER=standard_user
DEMO_PASSWORD=secret_sauce

# JWT signing key for the SUT (demo-shop-app). This is a genuinely SENSITIVE
# value — in CI it is injected from a GitHub Secret and forwarded to the app via
# playwright.config.ts (webServer.env). Locally it falls back to the app default.
# JWT_SECRET=change-me-locally

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AI test suite (opt-in) — LLM-as-judge + self-healing locators (see ai/ + ADR-019).
# The `@ai` suite SKIPS entirely when GEMINI_API_KEY is unset, and never runs in the
# default suite (it needs AI_TESTS=1 + `npm run test:ai`). Get a free key from
# Google AI Studio. In CI it comes from the GEMINI_API_KEY GitHub Secret.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# GEMINI_API_KEY=your-google-ai-studio-key
# GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash

